definitions.definition: Any of several trees of the genus Nyssa which grow in swampy regions on the eastern, southern and midwestern United States.

subdefinitions.definition: Nyssa multiflora , a North American tree of the dogwood family, with brilliant, glossy foliage and acid red berries.

main_definition: Any of several trees of the genus Nyssa which grow in swampy regions on the eastern, southern and midwestern United States.
